  "texts": [
    "In addition, we emphasized the importance of B-list festivals in being more open to films by women and their aggregate effects on increasing the thematic diversity of the festival circuit, enabling films to find their interested audiences internationally.",
    "This evidence, in terms of the value that different kinds of festivals provide to the wider international film industries, could be used by national and regional policymakers in designing the festival circuit and finetuning their public remits.",
    "That is, the potential use of the methodologies showcased in this paper goes beyond the research context and is foreseeable by both industry professionals and policymakers.",
    "The introduced techniques could be adopted by festival programmers interested in tracking the diversity of their programming across different dimensions, including gender, content themes, geography, and language discussed in this paper, but also others.",
    "Such analyses would provide an indication of a program's breadth and disparity between the included productions."
  ]
}